Author:
Vol / Page:  3
Edition:
Quote:  In the case in which a man was charged with a breach of a prohibition order, he being found in the bar of the Railway refreshment rooms, Magistrate James decided that a refreshment room was not a licensed house within the meaning of the Act, the license for refreshment rooms being now issued by the Minister for Railways, not by the Licensing Committee, as prescribed by the Act.
